# HLS Streaming Upgrade: Adaptive Bitrate & Live Readiness

I have successfully upgraded VibeStream's video pipeline to support **HLS (HTTP Live Streaming)**. This shift from static `.mp4` files to adaptive streaming ensures that users on any connection speed (from 3G to Fiber) get a buffer-free, high-quality experience.

## Technical Accomplishments

### 1. Multi-Bitrate HLS Engine ([lib/video-processor.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/video-processor.ts))
The new processing engine implements a modern **ABR (Adaptive Bitrate) Ladder**. When a video is uploaded, it is now automatically transcoded into 5 different resolutions:
- **1080p (6000k)**: For high-speed desktop connections.
- **720p (3000k)**: High-definition standard.
- **480p (1500k)**: Balanced mobile/web quality.
- **360p (800k)**: Efficient mobile streaming.
- **240p (400k)**: Ultra-low bandwidth fallback.

### 2. High-Concurrency Batch Uploads ([app/api/process/route.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/app/api/process/route.ts))
Since HLS consists of many small [.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/next-env.d.ts) segments, uploading them one-by-one would be too slow.
- Integrated `p-limit` to handle **15 concurrent uploads** to Cloudflare R2.
- Implemented robust cleanup that ensures no temporary video files remain on the server after processing.
- Added adaptive `Cache-Control` headers: Segments are cached for 1 year, while the master playlist is uncached to ensure instant updates.

### 3. Progressive Video Player ([components/VideoPlayer.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx))
The [VideoPlayer](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx#32-515) has been rebuilt with **`hls.js`** integration while preserving our premium, glassmorphic UI.
- **Ambient Sync**: The blurred background lighting still syncs perfectly with the HLS stream.
- **Error Recovery**: Automatic network and media error recovery (e.g., if a segment fails to load, it retries instantly).
- **Safari Support**: Native HLS support is maintained for Apple devices, with `hls.js` handling all other modern browsers.

## Phase 31: Live Streaming & Crypto Tipping

I have successfully implemented a low-cost live streaming solution and a direct peer-to-peer crypto tipping system.

### Key Accomplishments
- **Low-Cost HLS Ingest**: Built a custom ingest pipeline using the browser's `MediaRecorder` API and Cloudflare R2. This avoids expensive dedicated ingest services.
- **Real-Time Broadcaster UI**: Created `/studio/golive` for creators to start live broadcasts with one click, featuring real-time health monitoring and segment tracking.
- **Crypto Tipping (Direct P2P)**: Integrated a "Tip" button in the video player using `viem` and EIP-1193, allowing fans to send native currency (Polygon/EVM) directly to creators.
- **Wallet Infrastructure**: Added `wallet_address` to user profiles and updated [Settings](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/settings/page.tsx#14-357) and [Profile](file:///C:/GOLive/types/index.ts#1-21) UI to support management and discovery of tip addresses.
- **Verified Build**: Confirmed that all new routes (`/api/live/push`, `/studio/golive`, etc.) are production-ready.

