# SEO & Performance Hardening

To ensure VibeStream handles maximum internet scale efficiently, I've implemented high-impact, low-cost architectural improvements focusing on search discoverability and client performance.

## Technical Accomplishments

### 1. Dynamic Open Graph metadata ([app/watch/[id]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Walt%20&%20Carter/.gemini/antigravity/playground/sonic-zenith/app/watch/%5Bid%5D/page.tsx) & [app/profile/[username]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Walt%20&%20Carter/.gemini/antigravity/playground/sonic-zenith/app/profile/%5Busername%5D/page.tsx))
Videos and Channels are now fully unfurl-ready when shared on Twitter, iMessage, and Discord.
- Replaced static Next.js `<head>` titles with [generateMetadata](file:///C:/GOLive/app/profile/%5Busername%5D/page.tsx#9-56) functions.
- Every shared link dynamically injects the video thumbnail, title, and creator bio into standard Open Graph and Twitter Card tags.

### 2. Framer-Motion Lazy-Loading ([components/VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx))
The [VideoCard](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx#35-172) component now leverages a dynamic Intersection-Observer via Framer Motion's `useInView` hook directly tied to the client scroll position.
- **Zero-overfetch architecture:** Thumbnail images [(<img src={thumb} />)](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/settings/page.tsx#10-13) will completely defer loading until the user scrolls within `200px` of the component entering the viewport.
- Eliminates thousands of unnecessary network requests when the Home Feed is populated, resulting in a significantly faster First Contentful Paint.

---
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This upgrade makes VibeStream "Live Ready." The move to CMAF-ready segments means we can easily pivot to low-latency live streaming in the next phase.
